40|$|Abstract — Most Autonomous Underwater Vehicle (AUV) systems rely {{on prior}} {{knowledge}} of <b>beacon</b> <b>locations</b> for localization. We present a system capable of navigating without prior <b>beacon</b> <b>locations.</b> Noise and outliers are major issues; we present a powerful outlier rejection method that imposes geometric constraints on measurements. We have successfully applied our algorithm to real-world data and have demonstrated navigation performance {{comparable to that of}} systems that assume known <b>beacon</b> <b>locations.</b> I...|$|R
