40|$|Localization is a {{basic and}} {{critical}} requirement for wireless sensor network applications, e. g. target tracking, monitoring and intrusion detection. In the received signal strength (RSS) based localization method; the Cramer-Rao Lower Bound (CRLB) for the estimation precision can be calculated given the <b>locations</b> of <b>beacons</b> and parameters of signal propagation. We propose a sensor deployment scheme that optimizes the overall energy consumption of the sensor network with a pre-specified CRLB accuracy for a large scale RSS-based localization system. 1...|$|R
